history.content:
I was enrolled in one class and on wait list for another had a swap set up for them. This morning I swapped the enrolled class with 61c and I appear to still be on the waitlist for the other class that was originally supposed to be used for a swap. I tried to directly drop the enrolled class but calcentral freaked out because it said I would under the unit minimum, so I couldn't directly drop. Thus, I had to swap.

TLDR: swapping 61c with a class I previously had in a swap and was enrolled in allowed me to stay on the waitlist for the other class previously part of the swap. (at least for now. I will wait to see if I get a email from the enrollment people saying I still have a swap or not)

children.subject: OP here-- same, this is similar to what happened with me too. I now have a class with 2 concurrent swaps on it for 2 different courses, and I don't know what's going to happen to my other waitlisted course if I get into the one of the them. Anyone with experience on this?
